 amphibian declines: Is there a link? (2003) Divers. Distrib., 9, pp. 111-121; Daszak, P., Cunningham, A.A., Hyatt, A.D., Infectious disease and amphibian population declines (2003) Divers. Distrib., 9, pp. 141-150; Lips, K.R., Green, D.E., Pappendick, R., Chytridiomycosis in wild frogs from southern Costa Rica (2003) J. Herpetol., 37, pp. 215-218; Ron, S.R., Duellman, W.E., Coloma, L.A., Bustamante, M., Population decline of the Jambato toad Atelopus ignescens (Anura: Bufonidae) in the Andes of Ecuador (2003) J. Herpetol., 37, pp. 116-126; Berger, L., Effect of season and temperature on mortality in amphibians due to Chytridiomycosis (2004) Aust. Vet. J., 82, pp. 434-439; Burrowes, P.A., Joglar, R.L., Green, D.E., Potential causes for amphibian declines in Puerto Rico (2004) Herpetologica, 60, pp. 141-154; Piotrowski, J.S., Annis, S.L., Longcore, J.E., Physiology of Batrachochytrium dendrobatidis, a chytrid pathogen of amphibians (2004) Mycologia, 96, pp. 9-15; Retallick, R.W.R., McCallum, H., Speare, R., Endemic infection of the amphibian chytrid fungus in a frog community post-decline (2004) PLoS Biol., 2, pp. 1966-1971; La Marca, E., Catastrophic population declines and extinctions in Neotropical harlequin frogs (Bufonidae: Atelopus) (2005) Biotropica, 37, pp. 190-201; Ron, S.R., Predicting the distribution of the amphibian pathogen Batrachochytrium dendrobatidis in the New World (2005) Biotropica, 37, pp. 209-221; Merino-Viteri, A., Coloma, L.A., Almendáriz, A., (2005) Studies on the Andean Frogs of the Genera Telmatobius and Bratrachophrynus, pp. 9-37. , (eds Lavilla, E. O. & De la Riva, I.) Asociación Herpetológica Española, Valencia; Pounds, J.A., Crump, M.L., Amphibian declines and climate disturbance: The case of the golden toad and the harlequin frog (1994) Conserv. Biol., 8, pp. 72-85; Pounds, J.A., Fogden, M.P.L., Savage, J.M., German, G.C., Tests of null models for amphibian declines on a tropical mountain (1997) Conserv. Biol., 11, pp. 1307-1322; Poun